curl_time_total: 44.015691s

Warm-to-warm: Stage A 306.16 stmt/s vs Stage B 303.72 stmt/s -> -0.8%, i.e. flat/noise, not a
real regression (Stage A's own cold->warm swing was +8.4%, so this is well inside natural
run-to-run variance). jdbcQueryCount identical (13,325) in both stages -- the log config
change did not even alter query *count*, only (attempted) execution grouping, and that
grouping never took effect. This is the negative result: HHH logged "Automatic JDBC
statement batching enabled" at boot, but IDENTITY silently prevents Hibernate from actually
using it for these inserts (confirmed against hibernate-orm docs: "Hibernate disables insert
batching at the JDBC level transparently if you use an identity identifier generator" --
documentation/src/main/asciidoc/userguide/chapters/batch/Batching.adoc).

=== Stage C fix: V4__statement_id_sequence.sql applied ===
