NOTE: PLAN.md's expected log text was "Executing batch size: 50" — the real Hibernate
7.4.1.Final message is "Executing JDBC batch (50 / 50) - [Entity#OPERATION]" (confirmed
against the actual TRACE output, not assumed from the plan's paraphrase).

Per-run batch count reconciliation (13,303 statement inserts @ batch_size=50, flushed
every 1,000 entities): 13 full flushes x 20 batches-of-50 = 260, + 1 final flush of 303
= 6 batches-of-50 + 1 batch-of-3 = 267 Statement#INSERT batches, + 1
StatementRun#UPDATE batch-of-1 (the final status->COMPLETED save) = 268 total "Executing
JDBC batch" lines per run. Grepped count: 536 across both runs = 268/run exactly.

